P: What are the parameters? strings, numbers, characters?  Convert everything to string.

R: Do I return a string? No
Return a boolean value “true” if the string is a palindrome, false if not.

E: “anna” → true
    “Hello” → false
    “12321” → true	

P: Check if its a string or not and if not;  Convert all parameters into strings, 
Convert the string into an array of separate characters 
Reverse the array and then join it back into a string
Compare the original sting to the reversed string
If the org string is the same as the rev string; return true; if not return false

function isPalindrome(line) {
let converted = String(line);
let strArr = converted.split(‘’).reverse().join(‘’);
	return converted === strArr;
}

